WEBVTT

00:05.438 --> 00:07.646
<i>FLINT: I am suggesting
that we help each other</i>

00:07.647 --> 00:10.782
by an alliance of pirates and slaves,

00:10.783 --> 00:13.585
<i>bring down Nassau,
maybe bring it all down.</i>

00:13.586 --> 00:15.220
My name is Woodes Rogers,

00:15.221 --> 00:17.656
and I am the next governor
of New Providence Island.

00:17.657 --> 00:19.491
Spain... what did you
have to promise them?

00:19.492 --> 00:21.655
That I would secure the remains
of the <i>Urca de Lima's</i> gold

00:21.656 --> 00:22.994
and return it to Havana.

00:22.995 --> 00:25.163
<i>- VANE: You set aside some of the gold?
- RACKHAM: She did.</i>

00:25.164 --> 00:26.631
- How much?
- Mm.

00:26.632 --> 00:28.333
<i>VANE: A cache of gems.</i>

00:28.334 --> 00:31.002
Spain is willing to burn
Nassau to the ground.

00:31.003 --> 00:32.938
The only way Rogers can prevent this

00:32.939 --> 00:34.573
<i>is to find the cache and return it,</i>

00:34.574 --> 00:36.608
<i>which means if we were to find it first,</i>

00:36.609 --> 00:38.366
<i>we could dictate what happens next.</i>

00:38.367 --> 00:39.450
FLINT: Where's Vane?

00:39.451 --> 00:41.880
The militia arrived
before he could get away.

00:41.881 --> 00:43.615
<i>We had no choice but to run.</i>

00:43.616 --> 00:45.417
<i>BILLY: You cannot stay.</i>

00:45.418 --> 00:47.185
The war is going to follow that chest.

00:47.186 --> 00:49.187
<i>I'll go back and address the situation.</i>

00:49.188 --> 00:51.456
We're creating the appearance
of a man out of nothing

00:51.457 --> 00:53.258
<i>that the resistance against the English</i>

00:53.259 --> 00:55.060
<i>feels compelled to rally around.</i>

00:55.061 --> 00:56.962
<i>When he's ready, he'll
step into the role</i>

00:56.963 --> 00:58.430
<i>we've created for him.</i>

00:58.431 --> 01:00.799
<i>BEN: Does he have any idea
you're using his name?</i>

01:00.800 --> 01:03.435
Long John Silver.

01:03.436 --> 01:05.937
It's a hard thing to look
your successor in the eye.

01:05.938 --> 01:09.307
But as far as successors go,
your mother could do far worse.

01:09.308 --> 01:10.475
Charles is dead.

01:10.476 --> 01:12.611
<i>Governor in Nassau
hung him in the square.</i>

01:12.612 --> 01:14.980
The resistance in
Nassau is now underway.

01:14.981 --> 01:16.348
I think you and I both know who it was

01:16.349 --> 01:17.505
<i>that fashioned that noose.</i>

01:17.506 --> 01:18.729
<i>ELEANOR: I know this enemy.</i>

01:18.730 --> 01:20.752
<i>He took that cache with
the express purpose</i>

01:20.753 --> 01:22.687
<i>of compelling us to commit your force</i>

01:22.688 --> 01:24.322
<i>to a battlefield of his choosing.</i>

01:24.323 --> 01:26.558
<i>If you allow him to dictate
the terms of battle,</i>

01:26.559 --> 01:28.527
<i>you court a disastrous outcome.</i>

01:28.575 --> 01:29.930
[horse whinnies]

01:29.955 --> 01:31.643
Tell your governor!

01:31.644 --> 01:33.877
You tell him I'm coming!

01:35.501 --> 01:38.496
